What is NumPy?

It is the foundation of Machine Learning.

Almost every ML library is built on top of NumPy.

Examples:

Scikit-Learn ✅
TensorFlow ✅
Pandas ✅
OpenCV ✅
PyTorch (uses similar tensor concepts) ✅

Without NumPy...

❌ No Machine Learning

Real-Life Analogy

Imagine you have a construction company.

Before building a house, you need bricks.

Bricks
   ↓
House

Similarly

NumPy
   ↓
Pandas
   ↓
Scikit-Learn
   ↓
TensorFlow
   ↓
Machine Learning

NumPy is the brick of Machine Learning.


NumPy Array
import numpy as np

arr = np.array([10,20,30,40])

Memory

+----+----+----+----+
|10 |20 |30 |40 |
+----+----+----+----+

Stored continuously.

This is called

Contiguous Memory Allocation

That makes NumPy extremely fast.

Why "n-dimensional"?

NumPy can create

1D

[1 2 3]

2D

[[1 2]
 [3 4]]

3D

[
 [[1 2]
  [3 4]]

 [[5 6]
  [7 8]]
]

Array Attributes
import numpy as np

arr = np.array([10,20,30,40])

print(arr.ndim)
print(arr.shape)
print(arr.size)
print(arr.dtype)

Meaning

Attribute	Meaning
ndim	    Number of dimensions
shape	    Size in each dimension
size	    Total elements
dtype	    Data type